 page link to `/projects/{name}`\n- From project page, users navigate to `/projects/{name}/runs` for \"View all runs\"\n- Clear hierarchy: Landing Page â†’ Project Page â†’ Runs Page\n\n**Runs Page Documentation:** The project pages design explicitly addresses runs page changes:\n- Line 130-137 covers how runs should be displayed\n- Task grouping behavior documented\n- Both server and client-side rendering mentioned\n- API response structure documented\n\n### Conclusion\n\nYes, the docs do describe the runs page layout and navigation. If you're adding a breadcrumb backlink from the runs page back to the project page, you should update `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md` to document the new breadcrumb navigation pattern. The document currently shows the forward path (project page â†’ runs page) but doesn't mention a back navigation element."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a95f52357850542ba (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 33202\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 13294</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ad92cb8-7573-48d9-ae42-414182ed763c","uuid":"2220bf0d-d76f-4534-93cb-ea0858290ce0","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the /workspace/docs/ directory and any markdown files for documentation about the web dashboard, runs page, or project navigation UI. I need to know if any docs describe the runs page layout or navigation that would need updating after adding a breadcrumb backlink. Do a quick search.","agentId":"a95f52357850542ba","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the documentation findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI searched the `/workspace/docs/` directory for documentation about the web dashboard, runs page, and navigation UI. Here are my findings:\n\n### Relevant Documentation Files\n\n**1. `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`**\n- Comprehensive usage guide with CLI reference\n- Section on \"Web Dashboard Enhancements